1.2.1	IDE ( also called now PATA ) is a wide 40 ( or 80 ) conductor cable ( Some cables with 80 conductors have the same 40 pins on each end . )	St
1.2.2	There can be possible 3 plugs ( where a 2nd drive is connected to the middle connector - but that is NOT the reason for the 80 conductor possibility . )	St
1.2.3	SATA is a much smaller 4 wire cable with a small plug on each end .	St
1.2.4	Each cable can have only one drive connected .	St
1.2.5	The speed of SATA is faster than IDE .	St
1.2.6	The initial SATA ( now called SATA I ) was 150 MBytes/sec where the IDE was topped out at 133 MBytes/sec .	St
1.2.7	The newer SATA II is twice the speed of SATA I .	St
